caption.text:
Jetzt geht ja wieder ein richtiger zelda hype durch die gamer Gemeinde mit dem neuen Spiel für die Switch.
Ich werde es mir leider nicht holen. Mir gefällt das Design irgendwie nicht so richtig. Ich bleibe breathe of the wild treu. 
Nächste Woche ist wieder Frühschicht angesagt und nahezu alle mangas sind soweit weggelassen und dann wird sich wieder chillig auf der Couch in die Decke gekuschelt und Switch gezockt. 
Wenn ich nicht doch wieder neue mangas oder vielleicht sogar Comics finde 🙈
🌺
Habt ihr das neue zelda und was haltet ihr von dem game?

Hoy nos hemos pasado el día en nuestra meca y la de tantos otros: #Akihabara !!! Hoy es nuestro último día de Railpass, así que hemos aprovechado para hacer las compras importantes que teníamos pendientes. La figura de #psychopass es una regalo de Héctor 💖💖💖. Como ha visto que me ha gustado, pues me la ha regalado. 
El llavero de #ryosaeba lo he encontrado por fin tras llevar varios días viendo otros de la misma serie, pero la joya de la corona es la figura del mismo personaje que he comprado en #Kotobukiya . #cityhunter es una serie muy especial para mí y nunca he conseguido encontrar material relacionado con ella. Las fotos no hacen justicia a lo preciosa que es. Además, por ser el día de salida de la misma, me han regalado un set de cara y manos adicional. También me he comprado una #nintendoswitch con todos los accesorios. Me ha salido bien barata porque pese a ser una edición especial de Minecraft, dicho juego no está, pero me da lo mismo. Estos días iré buscando por las tiendas del barrio el Tetris99 y algún jueguito más. #elviajedemivida me está dando mucho calorcito rico en el pecho 😊😊😊

#ThrowbackTāite with The Last of Us.

Now I know this isn’t a real OG throwback but it’s been 6 years since this game first came out on PS3.  One of the best from the previous generation, it rightfully got a remaster early into the PS4’s life.

Probably an overstatement but I feel like this was the title to begin the downfall of Xbox’s battle with PlayStation for this generation.  The Last of Us began a wave of first party title hits that kept on coming, with Bloodborne, Uncharted 4,Horizon, Spider-Man and God of War following it over the course of years.

What made The Last of Us really amazing is the dark storytelling of the game.  Nothing goes right for the main character Joel, and that’s evident right at the start of the game (seriously, 10 minutes in and was shocked!). When Ellie enters Joel’s life, the journey they both undertake is a beautiful, dark , twisted classic.  One that rivals many storytelling told in today’s entrainment.

The VO and motion capture performances by Troy Baker and Ashley Johnson, two of the best in the industry, of Joel and Ellie are amazing as well and definitely add to the overall incredible game that is The Last of Us.  It’s also crazy to think that the developer that bought us Crash Bandicoot also bought us this treasure.

Please, for the love that is all good in this world, check this game out when it becomes free to download for PS Plus members in October!  You’ll thank me later!

I can't say that Princess Peach is my favorite character. But she's a princess from my favorite series 😉 When I was a child I loved to play Super Mario Bros. and Dr.Mario (and I love this games for now). I do not think that a lot of people even know about the second game. It's some kind of a tetris: you play as Dr. Mario and you need to destroy microbes in a bottle with medicine of different colors. Thanks to my Switch I can play it again any time I want. So what was your favorite retro games?
Не могу сказать,  что Принцесса Пич - мой любимый персонаж. Но она персонаж из моей любимой серии игр. Когда я была маленькой,  просто обожала (на самом деле до сих пор люблю) играть в Super Mario Bros. и Dr.Mario. Не думаю,  что  многие знают о второй. Она своего рода тетрис: ты играешь за доктора Марио и при помощи цветных капсул с лекарствами должен уничтожить микробы в банке. И благодаря свичу я снова могу в нее играть,  когда захочется (лишь бы был интернет ><)

I fell in love with the console from the first moment.
Nintendo has proven that it can create revolutionary devices.
Thanks to Switch, you can once again move to the world of beloved heroes from childhood, and their adventures are as perfectly as before.

caption.text: #nintendoswitchlite  #nintendo https://youtu.be/iI124k1-5M8 Ite  it’s here  my Unboxing of the Nintendo Switch Lite unboxing video... You can watch the full video on my YouTube channel. My link is in my Bio #nintendoswitch

Just finished Xenoblade the other day, and I must say that was a very impressive JRPG. Pardon the low-res picture; the 3DS doesn't have a screenshot feature (at least to my knowledge). Why bring up Xenoblade? Simply because it has a bunch of awesome mecha designs like the one you see above (the yellow one is named Yaldabaoth, in typical JRPG fashion). Tetsuya Takahashi and his wife Kaori Tanaka, the minds behind the whole Xeno series, are big mecha fans and all their games feature mechas one way or another. Xenogears and Xenosaga in particular have lots of awesome robots and it's a shame no model kits were released aside from the Weltall from Xenogears.

Aside from the cool mecha designs, Xenoblade Chronicles is a great JRPG with a gripping story, a vast and unique world to explore (the slumbering bodies of two giants on which entire ecosystems flourished), an exciting battle system and a remarkable soundtrack. If you have never played this game before, I recommend you check out the Definitive Edition once it comes out on the Switch!

This is an amazing remake. Link's Awakening has always been a special Zelda game. From what I understand, the team that developed the original had an absolute blast from start to finish. The love and passion shines in this game, and the remake brings all those beautiful sprites to life in a way that's not easily done.
Gameplay is flawless and this is a shot for shot remake, with the exception of Dampé, and his little build-a-dungeon mini-game, who has now officially been in more mainline Zelda games than Epona!  My only gripe is the same as everyone else's- the frame rate. It's not offensive by any means, but the stutter when you enter a new area is hard not to miss.
All in all, this is a flawless remake and must-have for any 2D Zelda fan.
9/10
